ties%20arrested%20Hindu%20monk%20Chinmoy%20Krishna%20Das%2C%20an%20ISKCON%20monk%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20who%20had%20been%20leading%20protests%2C%20on%20charges%20of%20sedition.%3Cbr%3E%5CnOn%2030%20November%2C%20a%20prominent%20Hindu%20journalist%20named%20Munni%20Saha%20was%20arrested%20by%20the%20police%20in%20Dhaka.%20After%20much%20outrage%20and%20on%20grounds%20of%20illness%2C%20she%20was%20released%20on%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20days%2C%20social%20media%20has%20been%20abuzz%20with%20pictures%20and%20videos%20allegedly%20showing%20children%20and%20adults%20in%20Bangladesh%20stamping%20on%20India's%20flag%20drawn%20on%20roads%20in%20educational%20institutions%20and%20public%20places.%20While%20this%20has%20naturally%20drawn%20criticism%20from%20enraged%20Indians%2C%20it%20has%20also%20raised%20questions.%20Why%20are%20people%20in%20Bangladesh%20showing%20their%20resentment%20towards%20India%3F%20Is%20it%20because%20we%20sympathise%20with%20the%20Awami%20League's%20Sheikh%20Hasina%3F%20Or%20is%20it%20the%20anger%20against%20Hindus%3F%20Or%20both%3F%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CPost%205%20August%2C%20there%20is%20an%20anti-Awami%20League%20and%20anti-India%20premise.%20Forces%20which%20have%20historically%20been%20against%20the%20creation%20of%20Bangladesh%2C%20against%20India%20and%20its%20involvement%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20against%20the%20Awami%20League%20are%20active%20in%20Bangladesh%20politics%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Sanjay%20Bhardwaj%2C%20Professor%20of%20South%20Asian%20Studies%20at%20the%20School%20of%20International%20Studies%2C%20JNU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMinorities%20%E2%80%93%20Hindus%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Christians%2C%20indigenous%20groups%2C%20etc.%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Bangladesh%20have%20never%20been%20safe%3B%20however%2C%20the%20ousting%20of%20the%20Hasina%20government%20has%20made%20them%20more%20vulnerable%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdded%20to%20this%2C%20Yunus'%20caretaker%20government%20has%20been%20placating%20Islamic%20fundamentalist%20outfits%20since%20coming%20to%20power.%20Yunus%20inducted%20the%20deputy%20chief%20of%20the%20ultra-Islamist%20outfit%20Hefazat-e-Islam%2C%20AFM%20Khalid%20Hossain%2C%20as%20his%20adviser%20for%20religious%20affairs%20in%20the%20interim%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20in%20a%20terrible%20situation%20since%20the%20fundamentalists%20have%20taken%20over%20power.%20Bangladesh%20is%20like%20Afghanistan%20and%20Syria%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20a%20senior%20journalist%20from%20Bangladesh%2C%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20as%20his%20accreditation%20was%20cancelled%20and%20his%20website%20blocked%20since%207%20August.%20The%20authorities%20have%20slapped%20a%20murder%20case%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20my%20country%20nowadays%2C%20you%20cannot%20say%20anything%20against%20the%20government.%20Speaking%20in%20support%20of%20the%20Awami%20League%20is%20treated%20as%20fascism.%20Supporting%20India%20is%20treated%20as%20terrorism%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%20senior%20journalist.%20In%20fact%2C%20Yunus%20has%20dismissed%20the%20recent%20violence%20against%20the%20country's%20Hindu%20minorities%20as%20%26quot%3Bexaggerated%20propaganda%26quot%3B%20with%20political%20motives%20aimed%20at%20destabilising%20the%20nation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CJamaat-e-Islami%20(JeI)%20calls%20the%20shots%20in%20Bangladesh.%20JeI%20believes%20in%20the%20ideology%20or%20idea%20of%20Pakistan%20and%20wants%20to%20pursue%20their%20politics%20based%20on%20Islamic%20nationalism%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Bhardwaj.%20%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20time%20and%20again%2C%20they%20have%20been%20Islamising%20Bangladesh%20and%20its%20polity%20since%20the%20split%20of%201971%2C%20against%20the%20ethos%20and%20values%20of%20India.%20They%20want%20to%20bring%20Bangladesh%20out%20of%20India's%20dependency%20culturally%2C%20socially%2C%20economically%2C%20and%20of%20course%2C%20politically%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Yunus%20regime%20has%20taken%20a%20series%20of%20anti-India%20decisions%20since%20taking%20over.%20The%20Dhaka%20High%20Court's%20recent%20decision%20to%20acquit%20BNP's%20acting%20chairperson%20Tarique%20Rahman%2C%20former%20minister%20Lutfozzaman%20Babar%2C%20and%20others%20in%20a%202004%20grenade%20attack%20will%20also%20further%20damage%20Bangladesh's%20ties%20with%20India.%3Cbr%3E%5CnRahman%20and%20Babar%20had%20collaborated%20to%20encourage%20anti-India%20insurgent%20groups%20from%20the%20northeast%20to%20operate%20from%20Bangladesh's%20soil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20economic%20front%2C%20Indo-Bangladesh%20trade%20had%20shifted%20from%20the%20traditional%20cotton%20and%20jute%20industries%20to%20infrastructure%20in%20recent%20years.%20Large-scale%20power%20plants%20in%20India%2C%20which%20exclusively%20supply%20power%20to%20Bangladesh%2C%20have%20been%20drawn%20into%20unnecessary%20review%20by%20the%20current%20establishment%2C%20much%20against%20the%20spirit%20of%20international%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorld%20Can't%20Be%20a%20Mute%20Spectator%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vandalism%20of%20Hindu%20temples%2C%20the%20arrest%20of%20Hindu%20monks%2C%20and%20journalists%20on%20sedition%20charges%20are%20violations%20of%20international%20human%20rights%20law%2C%20and%20India%20is%20perfectly%20correct%20in%20airing%20its%20concerns%20about%20the%20violation%20of%20minority%20rights%20in%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Western%20media%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20vocal%20about%20democratic%20regimes%20overthrown%20through%20anarchy%2C%20have%20been%20silent%20on%20Bangladesh%2C%20despite%20their%20well-known%20stance%20towards%20countries%20leaning%20towards%20radical%20Islam.%20Just%20yesterday%2C%20in%20the%20UK%20Parliament%2C%20British%20MPs%20Barry%20Gardiner%20and%20Priti%20Patel%20raised%20concerns%20over%20violence%20against%20Hindus%20in%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20recent%20criticism%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98barbaric%20attack'%20on%20Hindus%20gives%20hope%20of%20a%20shift%20in%20US%20foreign%20policy%2C%20which%20may%20be%20on%20the%20horizon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20has%20been%20silent%20on%20the%20ongoing%20human%20rights%20violations%20in%20Bangladesh.%20Historically%2C%20India%20and%20the%20US%20have%20been%20on%20opposite%20sides%20since%20Bangladesh's%20liberation%20from%20Pakistan%20in%201971.%20The%20US%20has%20worked%20over%20the%20years%20to%20undermine%20the%20Awami%20League%20rule%20under%20PM%20Hasina.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CUS%20Democrats%2C%20for%20their%20own%20reasons%2C%20don't%20like%20the%20Awami%20League%2C%20and%20they%20have%20also%20been%20working%20with%20the%20radicals.%20Now%2C%20Trump%20has%20strongly%20indicated%20concern%20about%20minority%20issues%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Bhardwaj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI'm%20still%20sceptical%20about%20how%20much%20personally%20he%20will%20intervene%20in%20this%20issue%20because%20the%20Pentagon%20and%20the%20deep%20state%20of%20America%20ultimately%20decide%20their%20policy%20towards%20Bangladesh%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3Cbr%3E%5CnIt%20is%20quite%20obvious%20that%2C%20with%20damaging%20India-Bangladesh%20bilateral%20relations%2C%20there%20has%20been%20simultaneous%20cosying%20up%20between%20Bangladesh%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%20announced%20a%20new%20visa%20policy%20allowing%20citizens%20of%20Bangladesh%20to%20travel%20to%20Pakistan%20without%20paying%20a%20visa%20fee.%20On%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20summit%20in%20New%20York%20in%20September%2C%20there%20was%20a%20meeting%20between%20Pakistani%20Prime%20Minister%20Shehbaz%20Sharif%20and%20Yunus%20on%20the%20need%20to%20%E2%80%98revitalise%20bilateral%20cooperation'.%20In%20October%2C%20Yunus'%20interim%20government%20scrapped%20the%20mandatory%20physical%20inspection%20of%20imports%20from%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%93%20a%20worry%20for%20India%2C%20as%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20the%20illegal%20supply%20of%20arms%20to%20militants%20in%20the%20northeast.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20in%20November%2C%20a%20cargo%20ship%20from%20Karachi%20docked%20at%20Chittagong%20port%2C%20marking%20the%20first-ever%20direct%20maritime%20contact%20between%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh.%20This%20was%20described%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20High%20Commission%20in%20Dhaka%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20major%20step%20in%20bilateral%20trade.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20in%20Bangladesh%20is%20volatile%2C%20and%20India%20will%20have%20to%20keep%20a%20close%20watch%20and%20react%20according%20to%20the%20unfolding%2C%20complicated%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(The%20author%20is%20Contributing%20Editor%2C%20NDTV)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733313300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2F1tb27fp8_bangladesh_625x300_01_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fbangladesh-is-sitting-on-a-powder-keg-7171051%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20a%20report%20by%20the%20Bangladesh%20branch%20of%20the%20Berlin-based%20human%20rights%20group%20Transparency%20International%2C%20minorities%20have%20been%20targeted%20in%20more%20than%202%2C000%20incidents%20of%20violence%20since%20Hasina%20was%20forced%20to%20flee%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22South%20Korea's%20largest%20labor%20union%20launches%20an%20indefinite%20strike%20and%20calls%20for%20the%20president's%20resignation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227979%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20gathered%20outside%20Seoul's%20National%20Assembly%20in%20South%20Korea%20on%20December%204%2C%202024%2C%20afte