0McLaughlin%20thinks%20that%20may%20have%20a%20trickle-down%20effect%20for%20homebuyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%20talking%20about%20the%20resale%20market%2C%20the%20existing%20homes%20market%2C%20it's%20hard%20not%20to%20become%20optimistic%20about%20just%20the%20broader%20economy%2C%20because%20of%20things%20like%20tax%20cuts%20and%20other%20benefits%20to%20households%20that%20might%20put%20more%20money%20in%20their%20pocket%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20McLaughlin%20said.%20He%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThat%20might%20encourage%20them%20to%20go%20out%20and%20either%20buy%20a%20home%2C%20if%20they%20don't%20currently%20own%20one%20%E2%80%94%20or%20grade%20up%20to%20a%20house%20maybe%20they've%20been%20waiting%20to%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2220565929-db8d-4853-9c3e-15da7357596e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHigh%20on%20supply%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20that%20backdrop%20mostly%20represents%20business-as-usual%2C%20next%20year's%20housing%20market%20may%20be%20marked%20by%20a%20significant%20development%3A%20sizable%20increases%20in%20home%20and%20apartment%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20long-running%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomic-inequality-housing-shortage-causes-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehome%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20finally%20easing%2C%20as%20Realtor.com%20predicts%20that%202025%20will%20be%20the%20first%20%26quot%3Bbalanced%26quot%3B%20housing%20market%20in%20nine%20years%3Cspan%3E%2C%20meaning%20neither%20buyers%20nor%20sellers%20will%20have%20disproportionate%20leverage.%20That's%3C%2Fspan%3E%20thanks%20to%20an%2011.7%25%20jump%20in%20existing%20home%20inventory%20and%20a%2013.8%25%20surge%20in%20single-family%20home%20starts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHome%20listings%20have%20been%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.realtor.com%2Fresearch%2Foctober-2024-data%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20rise%3