als%20started%20cutting%20rates%20at%20their%20meeting%20in%20September%2C%20and%20they%20lowered%20rates%20again%20in%20November.%20As%20the%20Fed%20continues%20cutting%20rates%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20should%20go%20down.%20But%20they%20might%20not%20drop%20as%20much%20as%20initially%20anticipated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20Low%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Low%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20have%20been%20elevated%20this%20month%2C%20and%20we%20probably%20won't%20see%20them%20drop%20much%20this%20year.%20But%20depending%20on%20how%20the%20economy%20evolves%20in%202025%2C%20we%20should%20see%20them%20ease%20a%20bit%20next%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20are%20unlikely%20to%20drop%20back%20down%20to%20the%20historic%20lows%20of%202020%20and%202021%2C%20when%2030-year%20fixed%20rates%20fell%20below%203%25.%20But%20rates%20are%20expected%20to%20go%20down%20throughout%20the%20next%20year%20or%20two%2C%20and%20it's%20possible%20rates%20could%20eventually%20settle%20in%20closer%20to%206%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Should%20I%20Refinance%20Now%20or%20Wait%3F%5C%22%3EShould%20I%20Refinance%20Now%20or%20Wait%20for%20Mortgage%20Rates%20To%20Drop%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20rates%20are%20lower%20now%2C%20some%20homeowners%20may%20be%20wondering%20if%20it's%20a%20good%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhen-to-refinance-mortgage%5C%22%3Etime%20to%20refinance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you%20have%20a%20high%20interest%20rate%20on%20your%20current%20mortgage%20and%20could%20save%20on%20your%20monthly%20payment%20by%20refinancing%20into%20a%20lower%20rate%2C%20it%20could%20be%20worth%20it%20to%20refinance%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%20are%20expected%20to%20go%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20further%2C%20you%20might%20benefit%20from%20waiting%20to%20refinance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20it%20makes%20sense%20for%20you%20to%20refinance%20ultimately%20comes%20down%20to%20how%20much%20you'll%20pay%20to%20refinance%20and%20how%20much%20you%20can%20save%20on%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Faverage-mortgage-payment%5C%22%3Emortgage%20payment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you%20save%20enough%20each%20month%20that%20you%20can%20recoup%20your%20out-of-pocket%20expenses%20relatively%20quickly%2C%20then%20refinancing%20may%20be%20worth%20it.%20You%20could%20also%20refinance%20now%20and%20then%20refinance%20again%20once%20rates%20drop%20further%20%E2%80%94%20it%20just%20depends%20on%20what%20makes%20sense%20for%20you%20financially.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20Do%20Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Work%3F%5C%22%3EHow%20Do%20Mortgage%20Interest%20Rates%20Work%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYour%20mortgage%20interest%20rate%20is%20how%20much%20you'll%20pay%20to%20borrow%20money%20for%20a%20home%20purchase%20or%20refinance.%20Each%20month%2C%20you'll%20make%20a%20payment%20to%20pay%20back%20the%20funds%20you%20borrowed%2C%20and%20a%20portion%20of%20that%20payment%20will%20go%20toward%20paying%20the%20interest%20you%20owe.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20portion%20of%20your%20monthly%20payment%20that%20goes%20toward%20interest%20will%20go%20down%20over%20time%20through%20a%20process%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fmortgage-amortization-schedule%5C%22%3Eamortization%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20you%20pay%20off%20more%20of%20your%20mortgage%2C%20the%20loan%20balance%20is%20reduced%2C%20lowering%20your%20interest%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20say%20you%20get%20a%20mortgage%20of%20%24300%2C000%20with%20an%20interest%20rate%20of%206.5%25%20to%20buy%20a%20home.%20Every%20month%2C%20you'll%20pay%20abo