0the%20most%20part%2C%20boomers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsick-leave-more-complicated-in-hybrid-work-era-gen-z-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewon't%20call%20off%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%2C%20they%20might%20come%20to%20work%20and%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BMy%20car%20broke%20down.%20I%20had%20to%20borrow%20my%20neighbor's%20car%20to%20arrive%20on%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20still%20made%20it%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20can%20be%20that%20way%2C%20too.%20When%20I%20worked%20at%20a%20restaurant%20in%20high%20school%2C%20my%20manager%20still%20expected%20me%20to%20come%20to%20work%20if%20I%20was%20sick%20%E2%80%94%20there%20wasn't%20an%20option%20or%20a%20second%20thought%20about%20not%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20might%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20my%20car%20is%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sick%2C%20so%20I%20can't%20come%20in.%26quot%3B%20They%20don't%20feel%20an%20overwhelming%20guilt%20about%20calling%20in%20sick%20when%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20some%20of%20this%20feeling%20stems%20from%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20For%20three%20years%2C%20we%20told%20everyone%20not%20to%20leave%20their%20houses%20if%20they%20felt%20sick%2C%20and%20the%20younger%20generation%20has%20carried%20that%20message%20into%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20some%20employees%20in%20the%20older%20generation%20dislike%20the%20younger%20generation%20for%20it%2C%20but%20I%20respect%20them%2C%20and%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20a%20bit%20more%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-work-life-balance-advice-boss-lessons-job-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework-life%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224289435b-6748-4560-96a6-0ea8e9fbcf5b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20To%20make%20small%20talk%20or%20to%20just%20not%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoomers%20and%20millennials%20are%20more%20known%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoronavirus-killed-small-talk-water-cooler-bad-for-business-happiness-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E'water%20cooler'%20talk%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20small%20talk%20conversations%20in%20the%20office.%20Before%20technology%20took%20over%2C%20that's%20what%20everyone%20did.%20You'd%20talk%20about%20the%20weather%3B%20we%20weren't%20all%20holding%20phones%20to%20entertain%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Gen%20Z%20doesn't%20feel%20the%20need%20to%20have%20those%20awkward%20conversations%20at%20work.%20They've%20grown%20up%20with%20a%20new%20form%20of%20distraction%20that%20previous%20generations%20did%20not%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECOVID-19%20also%20occurred%20at%20a%20critical%20juncture%20in%20the%20lives%20of%20many%20members%20of%20the%20younger%20generation%2C%20causing%20them%20to%20miss%20experiences%20like%20proms%20and%20face%20the%20challenge%20of%20attending%20college%20from%20home%20because%20they%20had%20nothing%20else.%20Due%20to%20this%2C%20they%20keep%20to%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20blame%20Gen%20Z%2C%20but%20older%20generations%20judge%20younger%20ones%20for%20being%20less%20social.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eac51c07-76b1-4c9c-b17e-effe21a2ebc1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20What%20they%20know%20and%20what%20they%20don't%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Z%20is%20tech-savvy.%20I%20consider%20myself%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-it-was-like-to-own-a-no-tech-car-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elow-tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20often%20ask%20my%20younger%20employees%20for%20help%20with%20my%20phone.%20They%20can%20also%20grasp%20new%20things%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20noticed%20that%20Gen%20Z%20sometimes%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Edoesn't%20know%20how%20to%20do%20other%20important%20things%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fhow-to